                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13482217" author="remast" created="Tue, 23 Oct 2012 09:10:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The corrected manifest where javax.servlet.jsp import is optional.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13507277" author="cvgaviao" created="Fri, 30 Nov 2012 11:34:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m facing the same problem. in my view optional is the best approach.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13633778" author="lhazlewood" created="Wed, 17 Apr 2013 04:41:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I resolved this by fixing the Import-Package statement in the web module&apos;s pom.xml (1.2.x branch and trunk):&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;Import-Package&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    org.apache.shiro*;version=&quot;${shiro.osgi.importRange}&quot;,&lt;br/&gt;
    javax.servlet.jsp*;resolution:=optional,&lt;br/&gt;
    *&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;/Import-Package&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If you see any problems, please let us know.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(JSP support will likely be a separate module in Shiro 2.x).  Thanks for the issue!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
